<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-89-0444 </DOCNO><TEXT>Renewable energy sources have been utilized since the very beginning ofelectric power generation. Advances in technology and increasing electricpower demands have been resulting in the further development of renewableenergy sources. The electric power industry of the Federal Republic ofGermany engages in developmental efforts like no other energy sector.According to the energy balance of the Federal Republic of Germany, about80 per cent of the renewable energy sources utilized serve for electricpower generation and district heating purposes. More than three fourthsof this share are used by the electric utilities. Access is given tothe major results of a VDEW member companies inquiry. Forecasts on thebasis of a DIW/ISI study refer to feasible renewable energy uses in theyear 2000.</TEXT></DOC>